This paper deals with the design of caching schemes for content delivery networks, which involves information theory, networking, and distributed computing. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory), cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture), and cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) are the most likely categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the benefits of coded multicasting, which is a technique used in network coding and can be related to cs.SI (Systems and Control) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
